Garcelle is stunned when her son makes an admission about her divorce. After leaving her mark on country singer Morgan Wade, Kyle is confronted by Sutton about the state of her marriage.

title: Wild Blue Yonder
overview: The Tardis takes the Doctor and Donna to the furthest edge of adventure. To escape, they must face the most desperate fight of their lives, with the fate of the universe at stake.

title: Episode 17

Dorit schools PK on their children’s future. Feeling let down by her friends, Kyle turns to sister Kim for support and advice about her family.

title: Episode 18
overview: While Deva waits for news from Fatoş, Agah continues to kidnap his family from Kader. Kader makes a choice between betrayal and revenge.

title: Mort: Ragnarick
overview: Heaven is for real, broh. I saw it, broh, I swear.

Bennett is arrested and held on an unrelated charge, while police continue to gather evidence against him. Newspapers vie for the chance to tell Chuck's story as media and police ignore issues in his version of events.

title: The Tiger
overview: Dot creates diversions, Roy meets his match and Indira helps a new friend.

title: Esopha-gate
overview: Crystal calls out Dorit for spreading rumors behind Sutton’s back, leaving both women fuming. Kyle seeks guidance from her life coach about her struggles with grief. Garcelle spends time with Jaid and his new girlfriend over dinner. Erika shares good news with her mother. The ladies come together to celebrate the anniversary of Sutton’s boutique as nurse anesthetist Annemarie goes toe to toe with her most difficult patient yet.

title: Willsmania

overview: Eager to improve the monarchy's public image, the Queen seeks out savvy statesman Tony Blair — but the Prime Minister's advice defies royal protocol.

title: Alma Mater
overview: Now at university, William sets his eyes on Kate Middleton. With meddling parents and other prospects in the mix, how will their connection bloom?

title: Ritz
overview: After a series of strokes, a declining Margaret recalls a wild night with her sister at the Ritz in 1945, and later celebrates her 70th birthday there.

title: Hope Street
overview: Reeling from loss and wary of her Golden Jubilee, the Queen bonds with William, who finds his footing between normality and life in the royal limelight.

title: Sleep, Dearie Sleep
overview: The Queen gives Charles the green light to wed Camilla. Tasked with planning her own funeral ahead of her 80th birthday, she faces an existential crisis.

title: Metamorphosis
overview: After rescuing Itadori from his predicament, Todo bolsters his morale and encourages him to stand back up. As Mahito kicks things into higher gear, he begins using Soul Multiplicity and Body Repel to unleash omnidirectional attacks.

title: Episode 19
overview: The Dog Killer, the Kandira case and more... With everything he has forgotten coming back to life in his memory, Agâh contacts a surprise name to become the hunter when he is the hunted.

title: The Nightmare 2 Days Before Christmas
overview: When the power goes out two days before Christmas, The Belchers must spend the holiday at Mr. Fischoeder's family's old hunting lodge.

title: The Return of The King (Of Queens)
overview: Lois decides to sell the family's television to help pay for Christmas presents, but when Kevin James gets upset over losing Peter as a viewer, he apparates into the Griffin house.

title: Into the Cold
overview: With the UN voting to outlaw independent spy agencies, Archer and the gang have to work outside the law to save the world from an unlikely duo.

title: Fear No Mort
overview: Only thing to fear is fear itself, broh.

Troubling errors in the police investigation also come to light and the Black community responds in anger at the prejudicial manhunt and the media’s handling of the story. Bostonians are left to confront the lasting impact of the Stuart case and to reflect on the enduring damage to their city.

title: The Tender Trap
overview: Lorraine calls things off, Gator asks questions, Wayne makes a surprising discovery and Indira offers a new perspective.

title: A Feisty Fiesta
overview: After enlisting a matchmaker, Sutton tries her not-so-steady hand at dating. Annemarie reveals which first impression left a bad taste in her mouth. Dorit is shocked at how far Kyle has waded into a new friendship. Tensions flare at Crystal’s Taco Tuesday between Dorit, Sutton, Crystal and Garcelle. Erika comes to a boiling point with Denise.

title: South Park (Not Suitable for Children)
overview: After it's discovered that a teacher at South Park Elementary has an OnlyFans page, Randy is compelled to take a closer look at the seedy underbelly of the world of online influencers.

title: Metamorphosis, Part 2
overview: The moment it appeared Itadori and Mahito's battle to the death was resolved, the being wearing Geto's body asked, "Shall I save you, Mahito?" Itadori immediately recognizes the man before him as the very same one who sealed away Gojo and leaps to attack.

title: Episode 20
overview: For Kader, who has returned to settle scores, now is the time to settle scores. For everyone else, the story is about to be rewritten.

title: The Church on Ruby Road
overview: Long ago, on Christmas Eve, a baby was abandoned in the snow. Today, Ruby Sunday meets the Doctor, goblins, stolen babies and, perhaps, the secret of her birth.

title: Linda
overview: Dot takes a fantastic journey.

title: Shibuya Incident - Gate, Close
overview: Choso begins to realize the identity of the mastermind parasitizing Geto's corpse as sorcerers gather for the final moments of the Shibuya Incident. The special-grade sorcerer, Yuki Tsukumo, comes to the rescue when they're on the verge of death.

title: Episode 21
overview: Agâh and Kader come to the end of the road with confessions and confrontations. It is time to say goodbye.

title: Blanket
overview: Roy’s campaign continues, Indira takes a stand and Witt tries to help.

title: Re-Lentless Erika
overview: Crystal’s Taco Tuesday heats up when Denise’s return brings back Erika’s fiery side. After rehearsing with her matchmaker, Sutton finds herself in tune with a new date. A tearful Kim asks Kyle to make amends with Kathy. After a war over words, Dorit and Garcelle meet one on one to hear each other out.

title: The Golden Wedding
overview: After lifetimes of love and loss and a whirlwind journey on “The Golden Bachelor,” Gerry Turner and Theresa Nist will walk down the aisle to begin their next chapter, happily ever after. Hosted by Jesse Palmer.

title: The Golden Wedding
overview: After lifetimes of love and loss and a whirlwind journey on "The Golden Bachelor," Gerry Turner and Theresa Nist walk down the aisle to begin their next chapter.

title: Mission Impossi-Bob
overview: Teddy gets stuck in an underground survival bunker, and he calls on Bob to find him and get him out.

title: The Useless Hand
overview: The tide turns.

title: A Celebration of Life
overview: The women head to Ojai for Annemarie's birthday, as frosting isn't the only thing Sutton is licking; Dorit questions her marriage after PK's shocking admission in therapy; Kyle hosts a celebration of life event for her late friend.

title: A Strange Situation
overview: Women from across the globe find love inside American prisons. In Germany, Svea prepares to meet her boyfriend, Joseph, for the very first time, despite her mother's reluctance. Single mom, Erin, leaves Australia behind and waits for her incarcerated boyfriend, Michael, to be released from an Ohio prison. In the UK, Emma surprises her family with news of her imminent US prison wedding to fiance Curtis.

title: Night Country: Part 1
overview: When eight researchers at Tsalal Station vanish without a trace, Danvers orders a search. After handling a workplace dispute, Navarro tries to convince a skeptical Danvers that the men's disappearance is connected to the murder of a local activist.

title: Bisquik
overview: Lorraine makes a visit and Dot prepares biscuits.

title: Bitter Pill To Swallow
overview: Kyle and Sutton unpack the group dynamics while planning their upcoming trip to Spain. Erika hits the ground running as she sets out to rebuild her career. Dorit reintroduces the group to Homeless Not Toothless and hopes it will be less of a mouthful this time. Crystal finds her voice when confronting Annemarie, and the repercussions echo through the ballroom.

title: Proposal on Parole
overview: Andreea, a Romanian student based in London, is set to marry Cage who is serving 50 years in a Texas penitentiary. But will her prison wedding go off as planned? Quickly following his release, Michael decides to propose to Erin with the ring she unknowingly brought from Australia. After some time back in Germany, Svea returns to America for Joseph's release but is alarmed by his future living arrangements.

title: Night Country: Part 2
overview: As Danvers and Prior learn more about Tsalal -- and find an unlikely location for the physical evidence -- Captain Connelly threatens to move the case to Anchorage. Later, Navarro and Danvers find a connection between one of the Tsalal men and Annie.

title: Tapas and Tattletales
overview: Adios Beverly Hills, hola España! Sutton takes the ladies on a fabulous getaway to Barcelona where Garcelle fears supernatural houseguests. Kyle's bold fashion choices leave Dorit questioning this new Kyle. Annemarie puts Crystal in the hot seat for talking behind the group's back.

title: I've Seen Him Naked Now
overview: Emma leaves the UK to marry Curtis in prison, but her clothing causes a major issue. Erin meets Michael's family in Ohio. Australian born Jessica is preparing to welcome home her incarcerated husband, Craig. Leaving prison after 11 years, Joseph and Svea check into a hotel for their first night--and his first bath in over a decade.

title: Night Country: Part 3
overview: While Hank leads the search for Clark, Prior asks Danvers about the murder-suicide case that drove a wedge between her and Navarro. Then, Navarro and Danvers seek out a local hairdresser for insight on Annie -- which leads to a tip.

title: Aches and Spains
overview: Hearts are racing after Crystal's medical emergency, but nurse anesthetist Annemarie comes to the rescue. Dorit opens up to Garcelle, allowing the two to finally move forward. Disappointed in her friends, Erika gets tipsy ahead of dinner but wows the group with her erudite observations at the table. While planning her healing ceremony, Sutton is overwhelmed by old emotions, forcing her to find comfort in an unlikely friend.

title: Second-Degree Engagement
overview: Lithuanian bride Gabriella faces criticism from her sister regarding her fiancé's second-degree murder charges; newly released Joseph moves into his cousin's basement in Michigan; Svea plans to go back to Germany.

title: Meet the New Farmers!
overview: The four farmers mutually match with women from big cities across the country.

title: First Date
overview: Meet the Smiths, John and Jane! Strangers who have given up their identities to be paired off by a secretive organization, both in espionage and in marriage. Two peas stuck in one pod. Come along as they run, jump, and adventure, making friends and making memories. But watch out, there's something amiss for this very first mission. It's John and Jane's: FIRST DATE! Good luck, John and Jane!

title: Second Date
overview: John and Jane are all dressed up with somewhere to go: a sinister black tie event. But first, the Smiths need ground rules at home: NO S-E-X. But when their wily target Eric Shane turns things topsy turvy, will they be able to set things right? It's John and Jane's: SECOND DATE! Bark bark.

title: First Vacation
overview: In their New York townhouse, in the bedroom, on the snowy slopes: John and Jane always have fun. And today, they're off to the Italian Dolomites. Will John discover a new hobby? Will Jane make a new friend? Are the two of them starting to really care about each other? John and Jane, it's time for your FIRST VACATION! Remember, another failure will make the boss very unhappy.

title: Double Date
overview: John and Jane aren't the only Smiths having fun. This time, meet Other John and Other Jane, another pair of Smiths, only they're SUPER high risk. But will the whole gang together be too much of a good thing? Double the laughs and double the hijinx! It's John and Jane's: DOUBLE DATE!

title: Do You Want Kids?
overview: It’s summertime, and John and Jane can’t wait to spend more time together. Join them in glamorous Lake Como as they drive cars, dodge bad guys, and chase after slippery Toby, whose naughty criminal ways have put them all in danger. But as they're taking care of this baby man, the two of them can't help but wonder, John and Jane, DO YOU WANT KIDS? Mamma mia, Toby!

title: Couples Therapy (Naked & Afraid)
overview: Oh, John. Oh, Jane. Our pair have been oh so bad at sharing and caring. Time to call in help -- John and Jane, get ready for: COUPLES THERAPY, what a gas!

title: Infidelity
overview: Hihi told John and Jane to take some space. John has been spending lots of time with his new friend, Bev. But what about Jane? Will John forget about all the fun they had together? Poor Jane! Bad, bad, John! How will John and Jane bounce back from INFIDELITY!

title: A Breakup
overview: John and Jane are taking a time-out. Will they be able to say they're sorry or will this be the end of their adventures? Grab some tissues John and Jane, it's A BREAKUP. Only this time, it's life and death. Don't be so dramatic!

title: Night Country: Part 4
overview: When Julia's mental health struggles resurface, Navarro brings her to a local facility, promising that this time will be better. Later, Danvers and Navarro confirm the location of Annie's murder, and Danvers levies a harsh punishment on Leah.

title: Atlanta
overview: Larry heads to Georgia to appear at the birthday party of a prominent businessman, while Leon takes the opportunity to visit his Auntie Rae. Later, Larry has some trouble with his glasses and faces off with a surly hotel cleaner.

title: An Earth Shatteringly Romantic Solar Valentine’s Day Opposites Special
overview: The Solar Opposites get romantic AF in their very first Valentine’s Day Special!

title: The Making of Shōgun: First Look
overview: The dawn of a new era. Watch for a First Look at FX’s epic saga of war, passion, and power.

title: The Making of Shōgun: Action Authenticity
overview: Hiroyuki Sanada (Producer / Lord Toranaga), Anna Sawai (Lady Mariko), and Eriko Miyagawa (producer) give fans a look at the action coming FX’s Shōgun.

title: Ashing It Out
overview: Sutton holds a healing ceremony for the group to let go of the past, but a shocking admission stirs up old grudges. The ladies say adios to Spain with a Flamenco dinner where Annemarie asks tough questions. Back in Beverly Hills, Kyle opens up to Dorit about the cracks in her once rock-solid relationship.

title: Collateral Damage
overview: As Craig finishes a 10-year sentence in Kansas, Australian wife Jessica is anxious about their first night together; Romanian fianc e Andreea receives harsh criticism from her family about her planned marriage to inmate Cage.

title: Don't Ever F**king Miss
overview: As Jake, Katagiri and Samantha pursue the truth about Polina, Sato clings to life – but not all of Chihara-kai are hoping for his full recovery.

title: Be My Number One
overview: As Jake and Katagiri seek new meaning at work, Samantha confronts a thief in her club, and Chihara-kai welcome a returning member.

title: Welcome to the Farms
overview: The farmers go on their first solo dates.

title: The World of Shōgun: History & Backstory
overview: See how it all began in “The World of Shōgun”. Experience the history behind the rise of Warlords, Samurai, and a powerful new empire in Feudal Japan.

title: Vought's Big Game Ad
overview: Today, Vought brings you an exclusive new ad for The Big Game. Rated "Too Patriotic" for TV, this is a love letter to AMERICA. Please enjoy with an ice cold Turbo Rush!

title: Night Country: Part 5
overview: As Prior digs into the links between Tsalal and mining company Silver Sky, Navarro rescues Leah from a local protest that has turned violent. At a meeting with Silver Sky exec Kate McKitterick, Danvers is warned not to pursue the case any further.

title: The Lawn Jockey
overview: Still in Atlanta, Larry finds himself stuck at a rental home with a questionable lawn ornament. Meanwhile, Jeff pays the price for taking Larry’s advice for Susie’s birthday gift.

title: The Making of Shōgun – Chapter One: Honoring Authenticity
overview: “You see it in each frame.” Find out how the Shōgun team brought unprecedented accuracy to the screen through collaboration with Japan’s most dedicated actors, artists, crew members, and cultural specialists.

title: Diamonds in the Rough
overview: Fresh off their trip in Spain, Sutton gets back in the saddle, both with her new horse and a second date. Garcelle agrees to give her boys more freedom, even as they prove they’re not quite ready for adulthood. Annemarie throws a blinged-out brunch where she and Crystal finally put their issues to bed. Erika’s tearful accusations leave Kyle and Dorit questioning their friendship.

title: Baby Steps
overview: Bride-to-be, Gabby, defends criticism from her sister regarding her imminent prison wedding; Erin and Michael begin to build a life together; Joseph is still living in his cousin's basement; Craig and Jessica have big news.

title: Lone Wolf
overview: In an attempt to gather information on the Grey Aliens, Harry puts Asta in harm’s way.

title: Old Law, New Twist
overview: Katagiri and Nagata ramp up their efforts. Jake gets invited to an exclusive party. Samantha and Sato deal with a growing problem at the club.

title: Tailgates and Tantrums
overview: The farmers and their chosen ladies go to a football tailgating mixer; tensions run high as both the farmers and ladies try to strengthen their connections.

title: Night Country: Part 6
overview: In the midst of a brutal storm, Danvers and Navarro find themselves stuck at Tsalal with no electricity or means of contact. As the truth about what happened to Annie and the Tsalal men unfolds, Navarro and Danvers each confront the demons from their past.

title: Vertical Drop, Horizontal Tug
overview: Larry’s improved golf game causes trouble with an acclaimed actor. Freddy helps his neighbors through a delicate issue.

title: Soirees and Separations
overview: After a tough year, Sutton celebrates her success with an over-the-top shopping day. PK’s continued absence leaves Dorit questioning her progress … and their marriage. The White Party is back and bigger than ever as Garcelle, Crystal and Annemarie get ready to watch Erika hit the stage at SoFi Stadium. A shocking headline forces Kyle to reckon with her marriage and leaves all of Beverly Hills questioning her truth.

title: It's All a Bit Messy
overview: German girlfriend Svea is concerned that Joseph, her formerly incarcerated boyfriend, no longer has time for her, while Craig and Jessica have money worries in Wichita. Olivia and Gabriella, both travel to Michigan for their upcoming prison weddings. And in Ohio, Erin is shaken when she discovers that her fiance, Michael, is hiding a huge secret.

title: The Upper Hand
overview: D’Arcy inserts herself into Harry’s mission, while Kate grows more uncomfortable in her own home.

title: Like a New Man
overview: As the new yakuza task force takes off, Ishida calls a summit. While Sato and Hayama join forces, Katagiri and Jake investigate a mysterious return.

title: You Need to Step up Your Flirting Game
overview: As the farmers go on their romantic second solo dates, the reality of their futures and life on the farm starts to set in; drama-filled dates with hard-hitting questions make some start to feel the magic or leave them heartbroken.

title: Disgruntled
overview: Larry finds himself in Takahashi’s crosshairs after a note is found in the men’s locker room. Tensions mount when Larry and Irma’s couple’s counselor crosses a professional line.

title: Anjin
overview: Destinies converge in Japan after a barbarian ship washes ashore in a poor fishing village. Meanwhile, in Osaka, Lord Toranaga finds himself outplayed by his enemies.

title: FX's Shōgun: The Official Podcast - Episode 1
overview:
Host Emily Yoshida and guests break down episode 1 of FX’s Shōgun. Featuring showrunner Justin Marks, actor Hiroyuki Sanada "Toranaga," historian Frederik Cryns, and costume designer Carlos Rosario. From cultural bonding and falcon training to dressing samurai and Dutch sailors, join them as they discuss the first chapter of the epic tale.

Join host and staff writer Emily Yoshida as she sits down with the creators, cast, and crew that brought Sengoku Period Japan to life. title: Servants of Two Masters
overview: Blackthorne’s arrival in Osaka stirs up a hornet’s nest of rivalries. Mariko is trapped between her cause and her faith when she must translate for the barbarian in Lord Toranaga’s custody.

title: FX's Shōgun: The Official Podcast - Episode 2
overview: A Taikō leaves his legacy. Host Emily Yoshida and guests break down episode 2 of FX’s Shōgun. Featuring executive producer and co-creator Rachel Kondo, actor Cosmo Jarvis "Blackthorne," producer Eriko Miyagawa, and director Johnathan Van Tulleken. Creators and cast discuss why some characters' names in the original book had to be changed for the show, why Ishido might be a sympathetic villain, and what Blackthorne sees in Yabushige. title: The Making of Shōgun – Chapter Two: A Day with Hiroyuki Sanada
overview: For the first time ever, audiences of FX’s Shōgun will see legendary actor Hiroyuki Sanada rise to a role he’s never played: producer. Join Sanada for a hectic day on set as he finds a balance between acting and advising, on a mission to showcase authenticity every step of the way. FX’s Shōgun premieres 2.27 on Hulu. Based on James Clavell’s novel, FX’s Shōgun is set in Japan in the year 1600 at the dawn of a century-defining civil war. Lord Yoshii Toranaga is fighting for his life as his enemies on the Council of Regents unite against him, when a mysterious European ship is found marooned in a nearby fishing village.

title: Reunion, Part 1
overview: In the midst of shocking headlines and hurt feelings, the diamonds of Beverly Hills come face-to-face for a tense reunion. Kyle addresses Erika's past comment about wanting Andy to "eviscerate" her on the couch. Dorit confronts Kyle about an ominous text message she received and the current state of their "close" friendship. Garcelle challenges Dorit and attempts to burst her bubble in order to get through to her. Annemarie swallows her pride when she apologizes to Sutton, but Crystal proves to be her most difficult patient yet.

title: Wedding Highs and New Lows
overview: After years of waiting, British bride Olivia is preparing to marry KJ in Michigan but drama with Emma sours the celebration.

title: 141 Seconds
overview: Harry tags along on Ben, Kate and Max’s family trip, hoping the mayor will lead him to answers.

title: Illness of the Trade
overview: After a disastrous setback, Sato and Hayama strategize a way forward. Jake and Katagiri pursue their target – and try not to land in his crosshairs.

title: Steers, Fears and Tears
overview: The farmers and their ladies head to Ty's farm in Sikeston, Mo., for a roping competition and hoedown-themed mixer; some ladies start to feel overlooked; it becomes crunch time to make a connection when the next solo date is up for grabs.

title: Fish Stuck
overview: After an incident at temple, Larry asks friends to vouch for his character – while also trying to help name a baby and worrying about a fish.

title: Tomorrow is Tomorrow
overview: After Blackthorne survives a brazen assassination attempt, Toranaga realizes he must ferry his allies out of Osaka or risk certain defeat.

title: Vought and Homelander Support Singer-Neuman
overview: Despite what the fake news might tell you, Vought and Homelander have ALWAYS been steadfast friends with Robert Singer and Victoria Neuman. This Tuesday, we're proud to stand with them, and work towards a new era for the SUPERhuman community!

title: FX's Shōgun: The Official Podcast - Episode 3
overview: A great escape. Host Emily Yoshida and guests break down episode 3 of FX’s Shōgun. Featuring showrunner Justin Marks, actor Nestor Carbonell "Rodrigues", stunt coordinator Lauro David Chartrand-Del Valle, and production designer Helen Jarvis. Listen in as Yoshida and guests explore the skills required to be a great samurai, how to drown on camera, and what it takes to build 16th century ships. Join host and staff writer Emily Yoshida as she sits down with the creators, cast, and crew that brought Sengoku Period Japan to life. In this exclusive companion podcast, each episode will break down the twists and turns of the plot, the top-of-the-line craft behind the scenes, and the real-life history that informed it all.

title: Reunion, Part 2
overview: The reunion continues as Sutton and Kyle's issues come to a head, jeopardizing their friendship like never before. The moment the conversation turns to Sutton's finances post-divorce, Annemarie offers her opinion on the situation. When Dorit addresses rumors about her marriage and reveals details on her latest robbery to the women, Garcelle finds herself in the hot seat for her questionable comments. As Erika celebrates her victorious comeback, she realizes that Crystal isn't so quick to let go of her past.

title: Cabin Pressure
overview: When the Griffins win a trip to Maine at Peter's company picnic, they decide to invite their friends on the vacation. Tensions run high and things soon spiral out of control when the cabin burns down.

title: What Did You Do
overview: Lithuanian bride Gabriella returns home to confront her family following her prison wedding to Jamal. In addition, Svea reconsiders her relationship with Joseph and waits for news of Curt’s parole decision.

title: Avian Flu
overview: Harry gets distracted from his mission, while Mike and Liv make a huge discovery.

title: I Choose You
overview: Chihara-kai attempt to regroup after a devastating shootout. Jake, Katagiri, and Nagata pursue a tip from Samantha.

title: The Making of Shōgun – Chapter Three: Creating the Costumes
overview: “The costumes tell a story of their own.” Costume Designer Carlos Rosario brings us into the process of constructing an ornate and authentic Japanese wardrobe for Shōgun, down to every stitch, brushstroke, and hand-dyed feather.

title: Jade in the Shade
overview: On a tour of the town's bootlegging history, Linda and Louise stumble into a treasure-hunting adventure. Meanwhile, Bob, Tina and Gene play host to a group of street performers looking to settle a beef.

title: The Gettysburg Address
overview: Larry tries to make better use of the time he spends in the bathroom. Susie starts a new business, and her advertising has unexpected results. Later, Larry gives acting advice to an A-list actress.

title: The Eightfold Fence
overview: Blackthorne and Mariko test their new alliance as they train Toranaga's gun regiment for war. Yabushige must navigate his past promises to Ishido when an old friend comes to the village.

title: FX's Shōgun: The Official Podcast - Episode 4
overview: A wall too high to scale. Host Emily Yoshida and guests break down episode 4 of FX’s Shōgun. Featuring executive producer and co-creator Rachel Kondo, actor Anna Sawai "Mariko," historian Frederik Cryns, and director Fred Toye. Join them as they discuss what Fuji's role as consort means, what's going on between Mariko and Blackthorne, and how to bring a small fishing village like Ajiro to the screen.

title: Crafting Shōgun | Behind the Epic Saga: Hiroyuki Sanada, Anna Sawai, Rachel Kondo, and More
overview: Every legend begins with a story. Join our creators and cast as they discuss the vision and artistry behind FX's Shōgun's groundbreaking series. Based on James Clavell's international bestseller, Shōgun brings Sengoku Period Japan to life, filled with war, passion, and power. We’ll discuss the traditions and authenticity applied to every scene, the complexity of evoking a time period in dialogue, the experts on set, and so much more.

title: Reunion, Part 3
overview: The reunion concludes with a surprise appearance from familiar face Kathy Hilton, whose presence draws mixed reactions from the ladies. Kyle recounts their difficult road to reconciliation and what it took to work through past wounds with her sister. Emotions continue to run high when Kyle opens up to the group about her troubled marriage.
